        }
    }
});

```

The key for solving this issue is to loop through the "DataSnapshot" object twice, using a call to ".getChildren()" method. However, this solution will **only** work if you create your own adapter. It won't work with the "FirebaseRecyclerAdapter". If you need to use the Firebase\-UI library, then I recommend you duplicate the data by adding all "bbbb" children into a single node. This practice is called "denormalization" and it's a common practice when it comes to Firebase. For a better understanding, I recommend you see this video, [Denormalization is normal with the Firebase Database](https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=vKqXSZLLnHA).

That being said, create a new reference to the newly created node, and pass that object to the FirebaseRecyclerOptions.Builder's "setQuery()" method. That's it!

